2. Introduction
This Cookie Policy explains how
delska.com
and its affiliates (collectively referred to as ‘
delska.com
’, ‘we’, ‘us’, and ‘our’) use cookies and similar technologies to recognise you when you visit our website, including but not limited to
delska.com
and any associated URLs, its mobile or localised versions, and associated domains/subdomains (‘Websites’), and/or when you use our Services. This Policy explains what these technologies are, why we use them, and the options for controlling them.
3. What is a cookie?
A cookie is a small text file that is saved on your computer or other device connected to the internet to identify your web browser, to enable analytics, and to store information about you, such as your language preferences or login details. We use cookies to improve the performance and functional capacity of the website. You can disable the use of cookies in most web browsers. However, if you disable cookies, you may not be able to access features of our website properly or at all.
4. Why do we use cookies?
We use first-party and/or third-party cookies on our Website for a variety of purposes, for example, to:
- Facilitate the operation and functions of our Website;
- Improve your experience on our Website and make navigation there faster and easier;
- Make it possible for us to create a customised user experience for you and to understand what you find useful or interesting;
- Analyse how our Website is used and how best to adapt it;
- Identify potential future clients and customise our marketing and sales interactions with them;
- Make it easier to tailor online ads to your interests.
5. What types of cookies are used by delska.com?
Cookies are divided into session cookies or persistent cookies. Session cookies expire automatically as soon as you close your web browser. Persistent cookies persist until their expiration period runs out or until you delete the cookie. The cookies have expiration periods set in them: some cookies may expire after a few minutes, others, after years. Cookies saved by the Website you visit are called ‘first-party cookies’.
Required cookies are necessary for the operation of our website and cannot be disabled on our systems. They are essential for you to be able to navigate the Website and use its features.
6. Cookies on delska.com
Our Website uses cookies to bring you the best user experience possible. We use cookies for various purposes. We use four categories of cookies, including required, preferences, statistical, and marketing. Each type of cookies is described below.
a. Required cookies
We use the required cookies to ensure the operation of our Website. These cookies are necessary for its basic functions such as security, network management, cookie preferences, and accessibility. Without them, you would not be able to use the basic services.
b. Preferences cookies
These cookies are used to improve the performance and functions of our website, but they are not essential. However, without these cookies, some features, like videos, may become unavailable, and you will have to enter your login details every time you visit the Website as we will not be able to remember that you logged in previously.
c. Statistics cookies
These cookies collect information that is used to help us understand how our Website is used or how effective our marketing campaigns are, or to help us tailor our Website to your needs and improve our Website.
d. Marketing cookies
Marketing cookies make it possible for us to understand what content you choose on our Website, to identify potential future clients and to personalise our sales and marketing interactions with them. Some cookies set up on our website are not provided by
delska.com
as a first party. Websites can be used to post third-party content for advertising purposes.
7. How can you manage cookies?
Most browsers allow you to control cookies through settings. However, if you restrict Websites in their ability to save cookies, your overall user experience may be impaired, because the Website will no longer be personalised to you. This may also prevent you from saving your preferences and information, such as login details. Web browser developers have help pages with guidance on how to manage cookies in their products.
If you wish to consent to, or change or withdraw your consent to statistical, preferences, and marketing cookies, click on this icon on the left-hand side of the Website.
8. Blocking and disabling cookies and similar technologies
Regardless of your location, you can also set your browser to block cookies and similar technologies, but doing so can block our required cookies and prevent our Website from functioning properly, as a result of which you may not be able to take full advantage of all of our Website’s functions and services. You should also be aware that if you block cookies in your browser, you may lose some of the information saved (such as saved login details and Website preferences). Different browsers have different control features for cookies. Disabling a cookie or a category of cookies does not delete the cookie from your browser, you will need to do this yourself in your browser. For more information about this, check your browser’s help menu.
9. Changes to our Cookie Policy
We may need to amend this Cookie Policy to accurately represent our Services and Cookie Policy. We reserve the right to change this Cookie Policy at any time without prior notice to ensure our compliance with laws, regulations, and governance rules. Any changes to the Cookie Policy will be published on the Website.
If you continue to use the Service, the updated Cookie Policy will apply to you. If you do not wish to accept this or an updated Cookie Policy, you can delete your account.
